-- Hess to cut back Port Reading refinery rates ahead of Sandy
-- 
-- Sun Oct 28, 2012 3:43pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/28/us-storm-sandy-hess-portreading-idUSBRE89R0HQ20121028

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Hess Corp ( HES.N ) said on Sunday it would begin to cut rates at its 70,000 barrel per day refinery in Port Reading, New Jersey, at 6 p.m. EDT ahead of Hurricane Sandy. 
 "We are taking the necessary steps to prepare our Port Reading, N.J. refinery for high winds and storm water," a company spokesperson said. Port Reading is located on a spit of land reaching up into the southern edge of New York Harbor. (Reporting by  Janet McGurty )